    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          1. All genders, admitted to UC San Diego Hillcrest Medical Center with an anticipated&#xD;
             remaining length of stay of ≥24 hours&#xD;
&#xD;
          2. Age ≥18 years at the time of consent&#xD;
&#xD;
          3. Requiring standard of care intravenous insulin infusion therapy at the time of consent&#xD;
             with an anticipated duration of intravenous insulin infusion ≥12 hours&#xD;
&#xD;
          4. Willingness to provide informed consent and follow all study procedures&#xD;
&#xD;
        Exclusion Criteria:&#xD;
&#xD;
          1. Current bleeding disorder, treatment with anticoagulants, or platelet count below&#xD;
             50,000/mL at enrollment&#xD;
&#xD;
          2. Lack of appropriate sites for sensor placement (sites must be free of scars, skin&#xD;
             irritation, surgical wounds, dressings, etc.)&#xD;
&#xD;
          3. Planned magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) study within 24 hours of enrollment&#xD;
&#xD;
          4. Any other condition that, based on Investigator's judgment, would jeopardize patient&#xD;
             safety during trial participation or would affect the study outcome&#xD;
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
